<br>
running is for the weak.  stand your ground, fight in, fight out... and die as a group if you must.  Have some honor, some cahones...  none of this running away crapola.<br>
<br>
And blood is right... how often at 51+ do you flee to the zone?  This skill is usefull for solo play or for pullers.  it is not what I would like to see my tank getting first.  I'd like him to have regeneration, and boost his stats.<br>
<br>
 <p><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, Leader of the <a href=http://www.tinkerspride.com>Tinker's Pride</a><br><i>There's nothing quite like an unexpected fireworks display... in a tinkers workshop!</i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vallaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/10/02 4:53:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA Speed Overrated?</span><hr size=1> AA is great to have, but I won't waste any bit of exp on AA till 60. Im a rogue. I pull a lot and I don't miss run speed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uartillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/10/02 5:35:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA Speed Overrated?</span><hr size=1> Sabbik people arn't saying get run 3 so you can run to zone to escape an over pull (ok some are becase that is a benifit) but the majority are saying get it becase its on ALL the time can't be dispelled helps with pulling helps with CR's and you HAVE to spend 6 points in the first teir before you can spend any in the next one up.  <br>
<br>
So what are you going to put those points into?  If you put 3 points in any of the skills like wisdom all your going to get is +10 to your wisdom for using 3 points.  <br>
<br>
Humm, I think I'd rather have a all the time 3% slower then jboot run speed and innate regen over any +10 to one stat.  If not getting run 3 becase you feel its only for fleeing to the zone you need to look at it again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 4:34:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA Speed Overrated?</span><hr size=1> For pullers, this is a must have.  Kiters too... especially wizzies as mentioned.  And while you can't always run away, sometimes you can, and it's great then.  Also, for the rogues... think of the CR.  You can sneak about faster, and that's going to come in REAL handy.  <br>
<br>
Besides, it's awful convinient.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 8:39:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA Speed Overrated?</span><hr size=1> Zarsiss is wrong? Fix me! My understanding is:<br>
<br>
NPCs (with very few exceptions) have 2 basic speeds. They are:<br>
1. Equal to, or slightly faster than an unbuffed PC<br>
2. ~ Spirit of Wolf speed or greater<br>
<br>
Run 1 will allow a person to outrun # 1 above. Run 3 will not outrun # 2 above. So, Run 2 and Run 3 are nice and all, but they might not be worth doing level 51 twice more for. Level will always be more powerful than any AA skill. For traveling on foot, I think most people would still want a SoW over Run3.<br>
<br>
I agree with the general consensus though. If you're determined to pick up 3 AA points, Run is the best place to spend them.<br>
<br>
I recommend you visit a class discussion board to find out what generally is accepted as the best way to spend AA points. Monks are pretty easy. <br>
<br>
Run 1 (optional R2,R3) <br>
Level 60 <p>Zarsiss Razorscale<BR>
Iksar Monk, 52nd Scale<BR>
Dreadstorm</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A> at: 4/11/02 8:49:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usilaena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silaena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 8:48:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA Speed Overrated?</span><hr size=1> I agree with Gore, <br>
<br>
  Whatever, I think people dont want to put xp in AA until lvl 60, except for those who need to stay 52- for epic/personal reason. Having Runspeed 3 is way better than having +10 in a stat I think, and since you need to spend at least 6 points on Basic AA I think I will go for Runspeed 3 Regeneration 3..<br>
<br>
  Just my 2coppers<br>
<br>
 <p>Silaena Shadeclaws Teir'dall Rogue<Br>
"TE MONEO VT QVIS QVEM VICERIT OCCIDAT"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 9:00:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/btk120/antoin.gif width=68 height=146></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well.</span><hr size=1> The thing that is attractive about run 3 is that you can pass jboots down on this server.  No more annoying camps--you can give up your jboots when you hit run 3.<br>
<br>
I would go Air 3 or First Aid 3, but Shadowknight's Bind Wound doesnt' go over 150 IIRC and I get Breath of the Dead at 49.  So no real point there.<br>
<br>
Regeneration 3 is always useful though. <p>--Captain Antoin Nolouj
<br>Knight of the Dark Oceans
<br>League of Shadows</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukratetheswifttail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krate The Swift Tail</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/thrawk/Krate.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 9:08:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well.</span><hr size=1> Gore has hit the nail on the head with this one, but since most people won't actually experience that part of the game, they're not gonna get it.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utresjoli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tresjoli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.shadow-striders.com/images/wolfIcon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elven Princess</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 12:31:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cpinternet.com/~theduke/MythStuff/ez-tres.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well.</span><hr size=1> I'm a level 60 druid on the Tunare server.  My first thought was, &quot;Why do I need increased running speed?  If I get in a pinch and lose SoW or SoE, I'll just gate or evac, right?&quot;<br>
<br>
Wrong!  At high levels lots of zones are indoors.  It is definitely not convenient and you're certainly not going to hold up your experience group or raiding party while you go to an outdoor zone to refresh SoW.  You're right, you probably won't often use increased run speed to escape monsters, but you will need it to keep up with the rest of your party.<br>
<br>
Jboots?  Horse?  If you've died and are on your way back to your corpse you won't have those those with you.<br>
<br>
Unless you solo a lot (which I understand is the case on Firiona Vie), you probably don't especially need additional run speed immediately after obtaining level 51 (although you'll probably want it before 60) unless you pull a lot in indoor zones, e.g., ToV.  <br>
<br>
As far as the rest of the AA abilities, they can definitely wait until after you reach 60. <p><b>Trésjoli Louveteau<b>
<br><i>Femme d'esprit</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uveloxiavoluptuous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veloxia Voluptuous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 569<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 12:52:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well.</span><hr size=1> Zarsiss... you never been to the Hole have you? heh... and in alot of the new and revamped zones, there are mobs that are faster than run 1 or 2, and as fast, or just SLIGHTLY slower than run 3. as far as i can tell, nothing can sow in the hole. so they gave certain mobs a speed increase, and some a decrease. Crusaders can keep up sometimes with run3, while rock golems are slower than normal run speed. warriors are about the same as run1.<br>
<br>
this isn't the only zone that this occurs in, but it is the best example. run3 has been a great tool, and often a lifesaver in pulling, running indoors, never getting it dispelled... it's one of the best things you can do with your exp. <p><BR><B>Baroness Veloxia Voluptuous </B><BR>
52 Halfling Warrior~run speed 3~regen 3<BR>
"Even the smallest person can change the course of the future" ~ Gandalf<BR>
*gnaws another enemy kneecap to shreds*<BR>Veloxia@hotmail.com<BR><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~2emiller/Sig4final.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthraallfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThraallFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/02 1:47:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1711.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well.</span><hr size=1> Run3 is a must i think for anypuller type class, Warrior/monk especialy.  Indoor zones = no sow/jboots/whatever, but still run 3 works.<br>
<br>
if you dont pull, its up to you<br>
